  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Five Forensic Pathways - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_five_forensic_pathways">Five Forensic Pathways</xref>
 is a 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_care_cluster">CARE CLUSTER</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_five_forensic_pathways">Five Forensic Pathways</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_five_forensic_pathways">FFP</xref>) are part of a currency developed to support the 
              <xref outputclass="supportingInformation"
               keyref="supporting_definition_national_tariff_payment_system">National Tariff Payment System</xref>
 for 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_forensic_mental_health_service">Forensic Mental Health Services</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_five_forensic_pathways">Five Forensic Pathways</xref>
 are 5 groupings of 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_forensic_mental_health_patient">Forensic Mental Health Patients</xref>
 based on their presenting characteristics and projected care package needs.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_five_forensic_pathways">Five Forensic Pathways</xref>
 are initially allocated on the basis of the pathway descriptors only. The allocation may be reviewed and adjusted if necessary on the basis of baseline measures.        </p>
  </div>
